<h2 class="bac">Our Business:</h2>
<p class="bac">
A division of Global Banking and Global Wealth Investment Management, the Global Corporate &amp; Financial Institutions Treasury Product Delivery team provides integrated treasury, liquidity &amp; debt solutions to Global Corporate clients and Financial Institutions. As a core member of the client team the Product Delivery Team partners closely with groups across Corporate Banking including; Product Management, eCommerce, Card, and Debt Product Delivery teams to deliver integrated solutions to our client. Treasury analysts work with clients operating around the globe with annual revenues of greater than $2.0 Billion, financial institutions and financial services companies. Client coverage is provided through Corporate and Investment Bankers who are aligned by industries and are partnered with Treasury, Liquidity and Debt experts. We are the #1 treasury services provider in the U.S. and a leading provider globally, serving 95% of U.S. Fortune 500 companies and 73% of the Global Fortune 500.
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Overview:</h2>

<p class="bac">
The program is designed to build strong talent for internal and external client-facing roles in Global Corporate Banking. The program emphasizes on-the-job training augmented by classroom instruction focused on technical, analytical and professional skills. Functional areas include treasury management, financial modeling and credit/risk fundamentals and relationship management.
</p>
<p class="bac">
Program Analysts complete rotations to provide broad exposure and understanding of key functional areas. Rotations provide exposure to treasury solutions, product management/innovation and risk management with intensive focus on how to best deliver innovative treasury solutions to our clients. As a member of the Analyst Program, you will have exposure to members of the leadership team and the opportunity to interact with our clients. Rotations are completed in the same city.
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Qualifications:</h2>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Candidates must have a Bachelor&#39;s degree with a minimum of six (6) credit hours of Finance and/or Accounting</li>
	<li>Candidates must have a demonstrated record of achievement, such as extracurricular activities or leadership roles</li>
	<li>Some common driving characteristics include: finance knowledge, excellent verbal and written communication skills, personal leadership, the ability to inspire a strong sense of camaraderie and technical skills such as Excel and PowerPoint</li>
</ul>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Training:</h2>
<p class="bac">
Virtual, web-based and instructor-led learning solutions are used to supplement the experiential development that occurs on-the-job. Throughout the program, analysts are provided a support network, which consists of the Program Manager, Rotation Managers and Mentors. An important part of this network are former college program analysts that now work in the different lines of business on the Corporate Banking team.
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Locations:</h2>
<p class="bac">
Positions are available in major markets across the Bank&nbsp;of&nbsp;America footprint. Line of business and location assignment is based on business need and candidate interest. Geographic flexibility is required at the end of the program in an effort to fill business-critical roles.
</p>

